            . I lodge in <placeName id="t18300415-345-crimeloc1867">Seacoal-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-345-crimeloc1867" type="placeName" value="Seacoal-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-345-crimeloc1867" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-345-off1865 t18300415-345-crimeloc1867"></join> - the prisoner slept in the same room; my hat was in the cupboard in the room. I missed it between nine and ten o'clock at night - he had come home between nine and ten, and went out again about ten - he had gone to bed, and got up again; he did not sleep in the same bed - I do not know whether he had undressed, but his bedclothes were turned down, and the bed was warm - I missed the hat directly he was gone; I went out, and found him going into a pawnbroker's shop with a white bundle, and asked if he did not lodge in Seacoal-lane; he said No (he had only been there four nights) - I asked him to come to the house, which he did; the landlord said he was the man - I then asked what he had done with my hat; he said he had pawned it in Turnmill-street, Clerkenwell.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. He promised, if I confessed, he would not prosecute me. Witness. I said if he had pawned it, and gave me the ticket, I would let him go - he said he had torn the ticket up.</p>
               <p>
            
